						               													<description>This is a variant to the free set up scenario of the game When Eagles Fight. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;Here we assume that as the &amp;quot;July Crisis&amp;quot; worsened, a change of heart came over the German General Staff to the point they abandoned their idea of first scoring a victory over France. Accordingly, they resolve to stand with two armies in Alsace-Lorraine and switch everything else to the East to win a quick knockout against the Romanov.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this scenario some units of the initial OB are deleted, and add 17 variant counters, plus 12 units from the reinforcements.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Other changes are that Central Powers are the first player each turn, and no receive turn 2 reinforcements.&amp;#10;Play stops after the victory check of game turn 2, and the CP must win with the normal victory conditions of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Published in Command magazine #26 (When Tigers Fight).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(source: rulebook and user's description)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
